reviewText: I had fond memories of this movie and was happy to see it finally arrive on DVD. While it was probably not an "important" film in any respect, the acting was very good and they really captured the small town vibe very effectively. Anyone who ever drove or attended a local race track is sure to feel the tug of good memories. Patrick Swayze's scene with the front end loader is worth the price by itself.
summary: Happy to see this finally made it to DVD
